    <h2>A Message from the CISO</h2>
     <p> As many of you are already aware, short passwords are no longer sufficient to protect sensitive data. While two-step login is on the horizon, we cannot wait until that is fully implemented to, at least partially, address the risk of weak passwords. While a longer password can be frustrating at times, a well-chosen sentence serves as a good passphrase that is also easy to remember. Therefore, NetID passwords for all DoIT staff will be migrating to passphrases over the Summer.
<strong>This policy will be enabled for DoIT NetIDs on Monday, June 12th.</strong> This gives everyone an opportunity to reset their password to a passphrase that meets the below requirements well in advance on your own timetable. Please note, the SOLAR self-service portal will no longer work for DoIT employees once this policy is enabled. As a result, you will no longer be able to reset your own password if you do not know what your current password is, or if your password expires without calling 2-9800 for assistance. To avoid this situation and any interruption in access, please diligently pay attention to the above requirements and your password expiration date. 
</p>
